From: Raffaella del Prete <raffaellanz@icloud.com>
Sent: Tuesday, July 8, 2025 11:04 AM
To: Grant Metson <Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz>
Subject: Re: 23 Mays Road, Devonport - Claim Process & Timeline. C90306048

Good morning Grant, Thank you so much for your email and for sharing the pr=
ocess document for my claim (C90306048) at 23 Mays Street, Devonport. I rea=
lly appreciate your effort to outline the framework and the chance to work =
together on this.=E2=80=8A


Good morning Grant,

Thank you so much for your email and for sharing the process document for m=
y claim (C90306048) at 23 Mays Street, Devonport. I really appreciate your =
effort to outline the framework and the chance to work together on this. It=
=E2=80=99s great to see the team involved, and I=E2=80=99d love your guidan=
ce on how we can move forward smoothly.

I=E2=80=99ve looked over the process map and have a few thoughts to ensure =
we get this right, especially around safety and planning. I=E2=80=99ve hear=
d from firefighters about significant fire damage and smoke exiting the roo=
f=E2=80=94initially thought to originate there by Devonport Flagstaff=E2=80=
=94which has me concerned about the house=E2=80=99s condition.

Could we please consider the following adjustments?

  *   Clarify Claim Scope: Is this the plan for both house and contents cla=
ims? If so, should it therefore be linked to both policy numbers to ensure =
all coverage is included?
  *   Prioritize Health & Safety: I=E2=80=99d feel more comfortable if we s=
cheduled independent assessments (electrical, structural, gas, moisture/mou=
ld) before any major work, alongside the July 9 asbestos survey. The master=
 electrician=E2=80=99s finding that the property is uninhabitable due to el=
ectrical hazards is a key concern.
  *   Assessment-Only Focus: As previously expressed, could we limit initia=
l tasks to enabling damage assessment (e.g., securing the site, debris remo=
val) rather than repairs (e.g., upstairs decontamination, curtain cleaning)=
? This would allow for a thorough evaluation and mutual agreement on remedi=
ation. The planned upstairs cleaning (July 21-25) feels premature for these=
 reasons:

     *   We need to assess damage before repair to preserve evidence.
     *   If the gas unit (likely damaged) requires removal, the ceiling may=
 need cutting, necessitating re-cleaning.
     *   The electrician=E2=80=99s uninhabitable ruling requires electrical=
 work first.
     *   Firefighters switched off water (possibly gas?) and electricity, w=
hich must be assessed and remediated.
     *   With 4 pets and hybrid work, noisy basement/deck/roof work makes l=
iving there untenable until completed.

  *   Asbestos Survey Details: While I=E2=80=99m supportive of the July 9 s=
urvey, could you please share who will conduct it, the scope and tests invo=
lved, and how I can independently verify the results? Also, can the funding=
 for this be covered under the claim preparation provision?
  *   Structural Engineer Guidelines: I previously asked about guidelines f=
or paying a structural engineer, as per the provision for claim preparation=
. Could you please provide these, as I believe an independent assessment sh=
ould precede any repair work?

I=E2=80=99d be grateful if you could provide a revised plan with a written =
timeline for expert sign-offs and re-occupation only after safety is assure=
d, preferably via email, by July 15, 2025. I=E2=80=99m really looking forwa=
rd to working with you for a safe and fair outcome.

Kind regards,

Raffaella del Prete


On 7 Jul 2025, at 5:31=E2=80=AFPM, Grant Metson <Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz<m=
ailto:Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz>> wrote:

Good evening Rafaella,
Thank you for taking the time to meet with me last week.
As discussed, please find attached a process document which outlines the fr=
amework of how Tower Insurance will progress your claim.
This is a framework only and the process will change, as we move through ea=
ch step, given that findings and results will affect the next step in the p=
rocess. This will be a live document that will gather detail as we progress.
However, I do trust that this will give you some insight and knowledge to a=
llow us to participate in the process together.
I look forward to speaking with you soon.
Please confirm back via email when you get a chance that you agree for Asse=
t Restore to undertake the asbestos survey on the 9th =E2=80=93 as this is =
the first step in the process.
Regards,
Grant.

[cid:image001.png@01DBF00D.0EFCA100]
