<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">Good morning Grant,<o:p></o:p></p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">Thank you so much for your email and for =
sharing the process document for my claim (C90306048) at 23 Mays Street, De=
vonport. I really appreciate your effort to outline the framework and the c=
hance to work together on this. It=E2=80=99s
 great to see the team involved, and I=E2=80=99d love your guidance on how =
we can move forward smoothly.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">I=E2=80=99ve looked over the process map =
and have a few thoughts to ensure we get this right, especially around safe=
ty and planning. I=E2=80=99ve heard from firefighters about significant fir=
e damage and smoke exiting the roof=E2=80=94initially thought
 to originate there by Devonport Flagstaff=E2=80=94which has me concerned a=
bout the house=E2=80=99s condition.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">Could we please consider the following ad=
justments?<o:p></o:p></p>
<ul type=3D"disc">
<li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-=
alt:auto;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1">
<strong><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Aptos&quot;,sans-serif">Clarify Cl=
aim Scope</span></strong>: Is this the plan for both house and contents cla=
ims? If so, should it therefore be linked to both policy numbers to ensure =
all coverage is included?<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"m=
so-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1">
<strong><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Aptos&quot;,sans-serif">Prioritize=
 Health &amp; Safety</span></strong>: I=E2=80=99d feel more comfortable if =
we scheduled independent assessments (electrical, structural, gas, moisture=
/mould) before any major work, alongside the July 9 asbestos
 survey. The master electrician=E2=80=99s finding that the property is unin=
habitable due to electrical hazards is a key concern.<o:p></o:p></li><li cl=
ass=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:au=
to;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1">
<strong><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Aptos&quot;,sans-serif">Assessment=
-Only Focus</span></strong>: As previously expressed, could we limit initia=
l tasks to enabling damage assessment (e.g., securing the site, debris remo=
val) rather than repairs (e.g., upstairs decontamination,
 curtain cleaning)? This would allow for a thorough evaluation and mutual a=
greement on remediation. The planned upstairs cleaning (July 21-25) feels p=
remature for these reasons:
<o:p></o:p></li></ul>
<ul type=3D"disc">
<ol start=3D"1" type=3D"1">
<li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-=
alt:auto;mso-list:l0 level2 lfo1">
We need to assess damage before repair to preserve evidence.<o:p></o:p></li=
><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom=
-alt:auto;mso-list:l0 level2 lfo1">
If the gas unit (likely damaged) requires removal, the ceiling may need cut=
ting, necessitating re-cleaning.<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" sty=
le=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l0 level2=
 lfo1">
The electrician=E2=80=99s uninhabitable ruling requires electrical work fir=
st.<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto=
;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l0 level2 lfo1">
Firefighters switched off water (possibly gas?) and electricity, which must=
 be assessed and remediated.<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=
=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l0 level2 l=
fo1">
With 4 pets and hybrid work, noisy basement/deck/roof work makes living the=
re untenable until completed.<o:p></o:p></li></ol>
</ul>
<ul type=3D"disc">
<li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-=
alt:auto;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1">
<strong><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Aptos&quot;,sans-serif">Asbestos S=
urvey Details</span></strong>: While I=E2=80=99m supportive of the July 9 s=
urvey, could you please share who will conduct it, the scope and tests invo=
lved, and how I can independently verify the results?
 Also, can the funding for this be covered under the claim preparation prov=
ision?<o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:a=
uto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1">
<strong><span style=3D"font-family:&quot;Aptos&quot;,sans-serif">Structural=
 Engineer Guidelines</span></strong>: I previously asked about guidelines f=
or paying a structural engineer, as per the provision for claim preparation=
. Could you please provide these, as I believe
 an independent assessment should precede any repair work?<o:p></o:p></li><=
/ul>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">I=E2=80=99d be grateful if you could prov=
ide a revised plan with a written timeline for expert sign-offs and re-occu=
pation only after safety is assured, preferably via email, by July 15, 2025=
. I=E2=80=99m really looking forward to working with
 you for a safe and fair outcome.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">Kind regards,<o:p></o:p></p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">Raffaella del Prete<o:p></o:p></p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<div>
